Package life.genny.qwandaq

Class Answer

  • java.lang.Object
    • life.genny.qwandaq.Answer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    @Entity
@QueryExclude
public class Answer
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Answer is the abstract base class for all answers managed in the Qwanda library. An Answer object is used as a means of storing information from a source about a target attribute. This answer information includes:
    • The Associated Ask
    • The time at which the answer was created
    • The status of the answer e.g Expired, Refused, Answered

    Answers represent the manner in which facts about a target from sources are stored. Each Answer is associated with an attribute.
